FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_CVRNAn exotic grotto has been discovered, and restricted planning permission grants you the opportunity to create a unique park in this hollowed out habitat! Building above the cavern is strictly prohibited, and guest numbers are limited, so you’ll need to conquer the depths to ensure this venture is a success. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_NOMOYou'll need to be at the top of your game for this one! The former owners have abandoned this park and left it in a real mess; negative cash reserves, a huge loan to pay off, ludicrous layout, and some seriously inefficient amusement rides. If you can turn this around it'll be a miracle. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_WNTRIt’s time to unwrap our plans for a festive-themed park in this jolly location. Just remember that your cash is a loan, not a gift! Spruce up your winter wonderland with seasonal scenery and draw in the merry crowds from far around. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_PHD1Chief Beef's Raceway was built on the site of an old seafront racetrack to take advantage of the site's heritage. Unfortunately, money issues arose during construction and concessions had to be made, and the resulting track has been deemed a disappointment by the public. Can you realise the site’s full potential? FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_PHD2This park has been thrilling the public for over a century, but it’s starting to be eclipsed by the towering, twisting thrill machines of newer parks. The board is keen to reinvigorate it with some exciting, modern rides while preserving its heritage. Are you up to the challenge? FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_PHD3Downtown Park was supposed to bring a little happiness to this notorious neighbourhood, where security guards demand higher salaries because of the increased risk, but the founder’s ambitions were undermined by the high levels of crime. Can you succeed where they failed, and bring some joy to the area? FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_DINEMiss Elly's Diner has some great facilities, including a big wooden coaster for a spot of excitement! But its remote location means it doesn’t see many visitors, and its potential isn’t being realised. Can you build on this location and draw in the crowds? FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_MARSThey filmed some pretty famous movies out here in the desert. It kind of looks like Mars, don’t it. The place isn’t much in demand any more – it’s all CGI these days – but the company doesn’t want to let it go. They want you to turn it into a theme park instead! FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_MINESome poor fella bought this mine from a prospector, and took out some big loans to pay for it. Turns out it was a scam. The varmint had salted the mine! Now he’s trying to turn it into a tourist attraction with some fireworks he was given and Old West-style streets, but it’s not doing as well as he hoped and he needs your help. Coaster_BoltBolt Coaster_Bolt_DescShuttle roller coaster, allowing the train to travel forwards to an end point before then travelling along the track in reverse back to the station. Coaster_DegenDegen Coaster_Degen_DescSpecially designed for inversions. Coaster_GnarlerGnarler Coaster_Gnarler_DescA traditional rollercoaster type that's primarily made of wood, which results in an exciting, rough and wild ride. This variant uses a more modern car compared to 'The Monster' Wooden Coaster. Coaster_PowerUpPower Up Coaster_PowerUp_DescA coaster where the train is chain-lifted vertically before then being inverted, which can also pass through the station multiple times. Coaster_SteelVengeanceSteel Vengeance Coaster_SteelVengeance_DescOfficial track of Cedar Point's Steel Vengeance coaster. Steel track and wooden coaster supports combine to create a hybrid coaster that can invert, whilst retaining the look and characteristics of a wooden coaster. ScenarioEditor_Staff_GeneralSettingsHeaderGeneral Settings ScenarioEditor_Staff_GeneralStaffProfileGeneral Profile ScenarioEditor_Staff_JanitorsHeaderJanitors ScenarioEditor_Staff_MechanicsHeaderMechanics ScenarioEditor_Staff_OffOff ScenarioEditor_Staff_OnOn ScenarioEditor_Staff_ParkRatingEnergyModifPark Rating threshold for Staff Energy decline ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_DefaultStandard staff settings: • Staff building perks provide normal bonuses. • Staff quit at their normal happiness level. • Staff start at their normal happiness. • Staff stop working at 15% energy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_EasyEasy staff setting: • Staff building perks have a greater effect. • Staff can quit at a lower happiness level. • Staff start at a higher happiness value. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_ApatheticWhen Entertainers are set to Apathetic:
• Entertainers don't increase guest happiness as much as normal. • Entertainers can entertain less guests at once. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_CommercialWhen Entertainers are set to Commercial:
• Entertainers don't increase guest happiness as much as normal. • Entertainers can entertain more guests at once. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_DefaultWhen Entertainers are set to default:
• Normal happiness increase for guests. • Normal Time between performances. • Normal amount of guests per performance. • Normal workload levels before Entertainers get stressed. • Normal pay and energy levels. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_EasyWhen Entertainers are set to easy:
• Entertainers increase guest happiness more than normal. • Entertainers can perform more regularly. • Entertainers can handle more workloads. • Entertainers don't tire as quickly. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_EnergeticWhen Entertainers are set to Energetic:
• Entertainers lose energy at a decreased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_EntitledWhen Entertainers are set to entitled:
• Entertainers require more money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_FatiguedWhen Entertainers are set to Fatigued:
• Entertainers lose energy at an increased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_GratefulWhen Entertainers are set to Grateful:
• Entertainers require less money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_HardWhen Entertainers are set to hard:
• Entertainers don't increase guest happiness as much as normal. • Entertainers have a longer delay between performances. • Entertainers get overworked from lower workloads. • Entertainers get tired faster. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_LazyWhen Entertainers are set to lazy:
• Entertainers don't increase happiness of guests as much. • Entertainers have a larger gap between performances. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_PassionateWhen Entertainers are set to passionate:
• Entertainers increase guest happiness more than normal. • Entertainers can entertain more guests at once. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_StressedWhen Entertainers are set to get easily stressed:
• Entertainers get overworked from smaller workloads. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_HardHard staff setting: • Staff building perks have a reduced effect. • Staff can quit at a higher happiness level. • Staff start at lower happiness. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Janitor_ApatheticWhen Janitors are set to Apathetic:
• Janitors are faster at performing tasks. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Janitor_DefaultWhen Janitors are set to default:
• Normal job durations. • Normal movement speed around the park. • Normal pay range requirements. • Normal energy levels. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Janitor_EasyWhen Janitors are set to easy:
• Bins have a higher capacity. • Janitors are faster at performing tasks. • Janitors can handle more workloads. • Janitors don't tire as easily. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Janitor_EnergeticWhen Janitors are set to Energetic:
• Janitors lose energy at a decreased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Janitor_EntitledWhen Janitors are set to entitled:
• Janitors require more money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Janitor_FatiguedWhen Janitors are set to Fatigued:
• Janitors lose energy at an increased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Janitor_GratefulWhen Janitors are set to grateful:
• Janitors require less money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Janitor_HardWhen Janitors are set to hard:
• Bins have a lower capacity. • Janitors are not as fast at performing tasks. • Janitors get overworked from lower workloads. • Janitors get tired faster. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Janitor_LazyWhen Janitors are set to lazy:
• Less effective at cleaning toilets. • Slower at performing tasks. • Slower movement speed. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Janitor_PassionateWhen Janitors are set to passionate:
• Janitors perform tasks faster. • Janitors move around the park faster. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Janitor_StressedWhen Janitors are set to get easily stressed:
• Janitors get overworked from smaller workloads. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Mechanic_ApatheticWhen Mechanics are set to Apathetic:

• Mechanics lose energy at a decreased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Mechanic_EntitledWhen Mechanics are set to entitled:
• Mechanics require more money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Mechanic_FatiguedWhen Mechanics are set to Fatigued:
• Mechanics lose energy at an increased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Mechanic_GratefulWhen Mechanics are set to Grateful:
• Mechanics require less money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Mechanic_HardWhen Mechanics are set to hard:
• Raises the breakdown threshold. • Mechanics are not as fast at performing tasks. • Mechanics move around the park slower. • Mechanics get overworked from lower workloads. • Mechanics get tired faster. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Mechanic_LazyWhen Mechanics are set to lazy:
• Slower at performing tasks. • Slower movement speeds. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Mechanic_PassionateWhen Mechanics are set to passionate:
• Mechanics perform tasks faster. • Mechanics have an increased effect on the durability of rides. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Mechanic_StressedWhen Mechanics are set to stressed:

• Security guards have a smaller radius of detection. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Security_DefaultWhen Security guards are set to default:
• Normal detection chances per report. • Normal detection radius. • Normal Running speeds and movement speed around the park. • Normal ability to handle workload. • Normal pay requirements and Energy levels. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Security_EasyWhen Security guards are set to easy:

• Security guards lose energy at a decreased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Security_EntitledWhen Security guards are set to entitled:
• Security guards require more money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Security_FatiguedWhen Security guards are set to Fatigued:
• Security guards lose energy at an increased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Security_GratefulWhen Security guards are set to Grateful:
• Security guards require less money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Security_HardWhen Security guards are set to hard:
• Security guards have a smaller radius of detecting crimes. • Security guards are not as fast when giving chase. • Security guards get overworked from lower workloads. • Security guards get tired faster. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Security_LazyWhen Security guards are set to lazy:

• Security guards have an increased chance to detect criminals from reports. • Security guards have a larger radius of detecting crimes. • Security guards recover from sprinting faster. • Security guards give chase at an increased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Security_StressedWhen Security guards are set to get easily stressed:
• Security guards get overworked from smaller workloads. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_DefaultWhen Vendors are set to default:
• Normal serving speeds. • Normal effect on on guest happiness. • Normal workload levels before Vendors get stressed. • Normal pay range requirements. • Normal Energy levels. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_EasyWhen Vendors are set to easy:
• Vendors can handle more workloads. • Vendors don't tire as easily. • Vendors are faster at serving guests. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_EnergeticWhen Vendors are set to Energetic:
• Vendors lose energy at a decreased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_EntitledWhen Vendors are set to entitled:
• Vendors require more money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_FastWhen Vendors are set to Fast:
• Vendors serve items faster than normal. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_FatiguedWhen Vendors are set to Fatigued:
• Vendors lose energy at an increased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_GratefulWhen Vendors are set to Grateful:
• Vendors require less money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_HardWhen Vendors are set to hard:
• Vendors get tired faster. • Vendors get overworked from lower workloads. • Vendors are not as fast at serving guests. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_LazyWhen Vendors are set to lazy:
• Slower serving speeds. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_PassionateWhen Vendors are set to passionate:
• Vendors serve guests faster. • Vendors have an increased positive effect on guest happiness. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_StressedWhen Vendors are set to get easily stressed:
• Vendors get overworked from smaller workloads. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Vendor_WorkBotWhen Vendors are set to Work-bot:
• Vendors don't have an effect on guests' happiness. • Vendors are faster at serving guests. FrontEndMenu_Difficulty_BeginnerBeginner FrontEndMenu_Difficulty_EasyEasy FrontEndMenu_Difficulty_HardHard FrontEndMenu_Difficulty_MediumMedium FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_CTKGCoasters! Building increasingly difficult coasters to satisfy King Coaster. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_GLLYThey said no one could build a theme park at Molly's Gully. Prove them wrong! Keep below the height restriction and bankroll the construction of a colossal coaster! FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_GOLMThe enormous golem's rampage has finally come to an end, frozen in eternal battle against the M.U.T.T.s. Our experts claim the creature is dormant, but local staff don't seem convinced; they're demanding a premium to work here! Utilise the monorail to make the most of the space and create a truly unique sci-fi theme park. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_KRKNRumours of engineers meeting sticky ends scared off this park's staff, leading to its recent sale. The bargain price presents an irresistible opportunity, so hire some new staff, complete construction of the park and ignore the reports of strange noises underground. I'm sure it's nothing to worry about... FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_MNLHA strange object found in the desert appears to have exerted an unexpected effect on the park’s rides – everything keeps breaking down and we’re running out of cash. Hire some mechanics, utilise work rosters to fix and maintain the rides, combat the Monolith’s power and get the park back in profit. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_NENCThe government recently sold off a tract of restricted land to private buyers, which was promptly snapped up by an ambitious theme park operation. Shortly after their grand opening, this sci-fi themed park's management mysteriously disappeared, along with all their research. Keep this park in the black, earn enough to research new rides and make this strange park a success. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_ODMLThis futuristic park's shop franchisors have questioned their long term commitment after underwhelming financial results. Retain their trust by squeezing as much profit as possible from your shops and facilities. Layout and pricing choices are key, and canny tycoons will make use of the ready-built shopfronts. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_PBTLAvast me hearties, and welcome to Planet Coaster! Shiver those timbers and take charge of this explosive pirate park. Complete ride construction, draw in the crowds and give your guests a swashbuckling good time! FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_PIRTFormer Pirate turned entrepreneur Peg-Leg Pete appears to be struggling somewhat; his loan-addled park is incomplete and lacking in fun (if only he could remember where he buried his treasure... It was around here somewhere). Take the helm and turn things around before this ship capsizes! FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_SKLLThe Skull? It appeared one day, rising from the earth in search of vengeance, I reckon. Some say it’s cursed but all I know is that it makes people unhappy. We need your help to counteract the skull’s effect or the park will never recover. Keep guests happy and keep them in the park. Hire entertainers, run marketing campaigns, do what you gotta do to keep the money coming in. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_SSMRThe Silversmith family are opening a theme park in the grounds of their estate to tackle their runaway debts. Your job is to build a successful park and keep the place afloat, with just a few caveats... The Silversmiths are rather old fashioned and will only allow ‘traditional’ attractions, so you may want to aim your Marketing efforts at families and ensure your ride sequences offer value for money. Oh, and build carefully, as the estate will take a percentage of any refunds... Good luck! FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_TGTRThey say this tree is the heart of the world. Can you respect mother nature and craft an eco-friendly theme park around the towering tree, or will you sell the woodland for profit and squeeze as much as you can from this verdant environment? TrackElementDesc_BarrelRollLeftOLD Barrel Roll Left Description TrackElementDesc_BarrelRollRightOLD Barrel Roll Right Description TrackElementDesc_BlockSectionAllows multiple trains to run on track at the same time, by stopping and holding them until the next section of track is clear.
For free sections to be available, 1 more block section is needed than number of trains.
Chain lifts and the station act as block sections.
Once added, block section mode can be turned on and additional trains added in the ride info panel's 'operation' tab.

TrackElementTool_BarrelRollLeftOLD Barrel Roll Left TrackElementTool_BarrelRollRightOLD Barrel Roll Right TrackElementTool_BlockSection<font color='accent'>Block Section</font> Allows multiple trains to run on track at the same time, by stopping and holding them until the next section of track is clear.
For free sections to be available, 1 more block section is needed than number of trains.
Chain lifts and the station act as block sections.
Once added, block section mode can be turned on and additional trains added in the ride info panel's 'operation' tab.
EFN values whilst on a block section do not contribute to the final EFN ratings for the ride. TrackElementTool_Booster<font color='accent'>Drive Tyres</font> Pushes trains along slowly.
